{"lemma":"ثَوْرَيْ","slug":"ثَوْرَيْ","root":"ث.#.ر","root_slug":"ث-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n4824"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bull, steer, ox"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Taurus (astronomy)","tags":["definite"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stir up, revolutionise"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ثَارَ (ṯāra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṯawr-. Cognate with Biblical Hebrew שׁוֹר (šôr)."},"ipa":["/θawr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4824","headword_ar":"ثَوْرٌ","root":"vwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bull:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaworapN","text_ar":"ثَوْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb:) pl. [of pauc]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowaArN","text_ar":"اَثْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyorapN","text_ar":"ثِيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyraAnN","text_ar":"ثِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyarapN","text_ar":"ثِيَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viwarapN","text_ar":"ثِوَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaArN","text_ar":"ثِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaArapN","text_ar":"ثِيَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA:) Sb says of the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyarapN","text_ar":"ثِيَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in it is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the kesreh before it, though this is not accordant to general rule: (S:) accord. to Mbr, they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyarapN","text_ar":"ثِيَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to distinguish it from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viwarap","text_ar":"ثِوَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqT","text_ar":"اَقط"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that it was originally of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolapN","text_ar":"فِعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M: * *) accord. to Aboo-'Alee, it is a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaArapN","text_ar":"ثِيَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~aworu","text_ar":"الثَّوْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The constellation Taurus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the signs of the Zodiac."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lord, master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K,) of a people. (A.) 'Othmán is called, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~aworu AlA^aboyaDu","text_ar":"الثَّوْرُ الاَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAbyD","text_ar":"الابيض"},{"kind":"text","text":"being added because he was hoary; or it may denote celebrity. (M.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stupid; foolish; of little sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stupid, dull man, of little understanding."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possessed by a devil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insane,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majonuwnN","text_ar":"مَجْنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so in copies of the K; but in some copies, [and in the CK,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junuwn","text_ar":"جُنُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diabolical possession,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insanity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"madness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA; and thus in Har p. 415.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large piece,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqiT","text_ar":"اَقِط"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has been churned and cooked and then left until it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become congealed and hard like stone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viwarapN","text_ar":"ثِوَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowaArN","text_ar":"اَثْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.)       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green substance that overspreads stale water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K;) this is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaworu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"ثَوْرُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuHolubN","text_ar":"طُحْلُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, T, S, M, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaromaDN","text_ar":"عَرْمَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galofaqN","text_ar":"غَلْفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small rubbish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken particles of things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the surface of water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the pastor beats to make the water clear for the bulls or cows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) Accord. to some, it has the first of these meanings in the following verse of Anas Ibn-Mudrik El-Khath'amee:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_in~iY waqatoliY sulayokFA vum~a A^aEoqiluhu\n                      \n                     \n                        kaAlv~awori yuDorabu lam~aA EaAfati Albaqaru"},{"kind":"page_break","n":365},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily I, with respect to my slaying Suleyk and then paying the price of his blood, am like the green substance upon the surface of stale water, that is beaten when the cows loathe the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but accord. to others, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alvwr","text_ar":"الثور"},{"kind":"text","text":"the poet means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bull;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the cows follow him: (M, TA:) the cows are not beaten, because they have milk; but the bull is beaten that they may be frightened and therefore drink. (S.) [See a slightly-different reading, and remarks thereon, in Ham p. 416: and see Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 330. The latter hemistich is used as a prov., applied to him who is punished for the offence of another.] ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pimples,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small pustules, breaking out in the mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a person who is fevered. (A.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"redness shining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAy^irapN","text_ar":"نَايِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spreading and rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaAy^irapN","text_ar":"ثَايِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the faint light that is seen above the horizon between sunset and nightfall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaworu Al$~afaqi","text_ar":"ثَوْرُ الشَّفَقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spreading appearance of the redness above the horizon after sunset."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqaTa vaworu Al$~afaqi","text_ar":"سَقَطَ ثَوْرُ الشَّفَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The spreading appearance of the redness above the horizon after sunset sank down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, A.) With its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suquwT","text_ar":"سُقُوط"},{"kind":"text","text":"commences the time of the prayer of nightfall. (TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness in the lower part of the nail"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","T","TA","A","Mgh","AZ"]}]}}